<paragraph id="1F2036C0FF82663EFF1F327DA568F9DA" blockId="7.[151,293,1630,1656]" box="[151,293,1630,1656]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
<heading id="446881ACFF82663EFF1F327DA568F9DA" bold="true" box="[151,293,1630,1656]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" reason="1">
<emphasis id="2DEBEAD2FF82663EFF1F327DA568F9DA" bold="true" box="[151,293,1630,1656]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
<taxonomicName id="D89F4D43FF82663EFF1F327DA4B6F9DA" box="[151,251,1630,1656]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2DEBEAD2FF82663EFF1F327DA4B6F9DA" bold="true" box="[151,251,1630,1656]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Drusilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp.
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1F2036C0FF82663EFF1F32BCA1D7F914" blockId="7.[151,1436,1694,2031]" box="[151,1434,1694,1719]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
At the present time it is not possible to confidently distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="D89F4D43FF82663EFCDE32BCA7ACF914" box="[854,993,1695,1718]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nearctica">
<emphasis id="2DEBEAD2FF82663EFCDE32BCA7ACF914" box="[854,993,1695,1718]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">D. nearctica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D89F4D43FF82663EFB9032BDA01EF914" box="[1048,1107,1694,1718]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ashei">
<emphasis id="2DEBEAD2FF82663EFB9032BDA01EF914" box="[1048,1107,1694,1718]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">ashei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
other than by male genitalia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1F2036C0FF82663EFF4F32E1A6EAF8C1" blockId="7.[151,1436,1694,2031]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
It is of interest that the North Carolina series of 
<taxonomicName id="D89F4D43FF82663EFD6832E2A770F97B" box="[736,829,1729,1753]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2DEBEAD2FF82663EFD6832E2A770F97B" box="[736,829,1729,1753]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Drusilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, hitherto described as 
<taxonomicName id="D89F4D43FF82663EFBB232E1A0DAF97B" box="[1082,1175,1729,1753]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ashei">
<emphasis id="2DEBEAD2FF82663EFBB232E1A0DAF97B" box="[1082,1175,1729,1753]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">D. ashei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, all have an abdominal tergal macrochaetotaxy (segments II–VIII, excluding paratergites) of 
<number id="A95724E7FF82663EFC3532C0A7A9F959" box="[957,996,1763,1787]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2-4</number>
- 
<date id="6B211000FF82663EFC6432C0A01CF959" box="[1004,1105,1763,1787]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="2010-04-04" valueMax="2010-04-04" valueMin="2010-04-04">
<number id="A95724E7FF82663EFC6432C0A7B1F959" box="[1004,1020,1763,1787]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="4.0">4</number>
- 
<number id="A95724E7FF82663EFB8C32C0A059F959" box="[1028,1044,1763,1787]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="4.0">4</number>
- 
<number id="A95724E7FF82663EFB9432C0A01CF959" box="[1052,1105,1763,1787]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="7.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="4.0">4-10</number>
</date>
- 
<number id="A95724E7FF82663EFBD232C0A024F959" box="[1114,1129,1763,1787]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="6.0">6</number>
. Conversely, the Arkansas series, hitherto designated as 
<taxonomicName id="D89F4D43FF82663EFE6D3324A63FF8BC" box="[485,626,1799,1822]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nearctica">
<emphasis id="2DEBEAD2FF82663EFE6D3324A63FF8BC" box="[485,626,1799,1822]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">D. nearctica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, all have an abdominal tergal macrochaetotaxy of 
<number id="A95724E7FF82663EFB3B3325A096F8BC" box="[1203,1243,1798,1822]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2-4</number>
- 
<date id="6B211000FF82663EFB6B3325A10AF8BC" box="[1251,1351,1798,1822]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="2010-04-06" valueMax="2010-04-06" valueMin="2010-04-06">
<number id="A95724E7FF82663EFB6B3325A147F8BC" box="[1251,1290,1798,1822]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4-6</number>
- 
<number id="A95724E7FF82663EFA9A3325A10AF8BC" box="[1298,1351,1798,1822]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="8.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="6.0">6-10</number>
</date>
- 
<number id="A95724E7FF82663EFAC73325A113F8BC" box="[1359,1374,1798,1822]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="6.0">6</number>
. This 
<taxonomicName id="D89F4D43FF82663EFF1F3309A54DF8E3" box="[151,256,1834,1857]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nearctica">
<emphasis id="2DEBEAD2FF82663EFF1F3309A54DF8E3" box="[151,256,1834,1857]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">nearctica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-macrochaetotaxy also applies to all female series from Oklahoma and three singleton female specimens from Kentucky, South Carolina and Tennessee.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1F2036C0FF82663EFF4F334CA09EF84C" blockId="7.[151,1436,1694,2031]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
It seems likely that 
<bibRefCitation id="7B0E4B31FF82663EFE2C334DA69DF824" box="[420,720,1902,1926]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" refString="Newton, A. F., Thayer, M. K., Ashe, J. S. &amp; Chandler, D. S. (2000) Staphylinidae Latreille, 1802. In: Arnett, R. H. &amp; Thomas, M. C. (Eds.). American Beeltes. Vol. 1. Archostemata, Myxophaga, Adephaga, Polyphaga: Staphyliniformia. CRC Press, Boca Raton, pp. 272 - 418." type="book chapter">
Ashe (Newton 
<emphasis id="2DEBEAD2FF82663EFDC7334CA6C5F824" box="[591,648,1902,1926]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">et al.</emphasis>
<number id="A95724E7FF82663EFD07334DA684F824" box="[655,713,1902,1926]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="2000.0">2000</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
was referring to the above Oklahoma specimens as a third species. Overall color pattern and macrochaetotaxy would suggest that the Oklahoma series is conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="D89F4D43FF82663EFA0933B1A54DF86E" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nearctica">
<emphasis id="2DEBEAD2FF82663EFA0933B1A54DF86E" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">D. nearctica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but species of 
<taxonomicName id="D89F4D43FF82663EFE373397A651F86E" box="[447,540,1972,1996]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2DEBEAD2FF82663EFE373397A651F86E" box="[447,540,1972,1996]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Drusilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
tend to be externally cryptic (Maruyama, personal communication; personal observations) and a series containing both sexes is necessary to make any definitive conclusions.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1F2036C0FF8D6631FF4F34B4A711FF76" blockId="8.[151,1436,151,464]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">Unidentifiable series of females are listed below to promote future work. Further collecting efforts must be made to understand morphological variation and species limits.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
